</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C370656FFFAEFF9BFF5B4C02521EFC41" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BD536E4FFAEFF9BFF5B4C025512FCF1" blockId="34.[151,1437,692,1112]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
DISTRIBUTION. A discontinuous range; the western part in NE 
<collectingCountry id="F37D7674FFAEFF9BFCB44C0255DDFC9B" box="[888,933,800,823]" name="Iran" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Iran</collectingCountry>
and S 
<collectingCountry id="F37D7674FFAEFF9BFC334C3D52E3FC94" box="[1023,1179,799,824]" name="Turkmenistan" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Turkmenistan</collectingCountry>
is separated from the populations in N 
<collectingCountry id="F37D7674FFAEFF9BFE944C66579CFCF1" box="[344,484,836,861]" name="Afghanistan" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Afghanistan</collectingCountry>
, SW 
<collectingCountry id="F37D7674FFAEFF9BFDEC4C6654EBFCF1" box="[544,659,836,861]" name="Tajikistan" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Tajikistan</collectingCountry>
, and S 
<collectingCountry id="F37D7674FFAEFF9BFD284C66551EFCF1" box="[740,870,836,861]" name="Uzbekistan" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Uzbekistan</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD536E4FFAEFF9BFF5B4C4A52A8FC0F" blockId="34.[151,1437,692,1112]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<materialsCitation id="3B023CB9FFAEFF9BFF5B4C4A5401FC09" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3342274498" country="Iran" location="Baluchistan Prov." pageId="34" pageNumber="35" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Khorasan-e Jonubi">
DISTRIBUTION IN 
<collectingCountry id="F37D7674FFAEFF9BFEA84C4A57E4FCD3" box="[356,412,872,895]" name="Iran" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">IRAN</collectingCountry>
. 
<figureCitation id="13512A61FFAEFF9BFE614C45544BFC2C" box="[429,563,871,896]" captionStart="FIGURES 98–103. 98" captionStartId="88.[151,264,1557,1580]" captionTargetBox="[171,1416,213,1516]" captionTargetId="figure-53@88.[151,1436,193,1536]" captionTargetPageId="88" captionText="FIGURES 98–103. 98. Eremias lineolata. 99. Eremias montana. 100. Eremias nigrocellata. 101. Eremias nova. 102. Eremias papenfussi. 103. Eremias persica." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4929754" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4929754/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Fig. 100. A</figureCitation>
belt along the Afghan and Turkmen borders from northernmost Sistan and 
<location id="8EB5603FFFAEFF9BFF5B4CAE5726FC0F" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03C387F2FFAEFF9BFF5B4D9654B6FBF4:8EB5603FFFAEFF9BFF5B4CAE5726FC0F" box="[151,350,908,933]" country="Iran" name="Baluchistan Prov." pageId="34" pageNumber="35" stateProvince="Khorasan-e Jonubi">Baluchistan Prov.</location>
through 
<collectingRegion id="49AEF806FFAEFF9BFE0F4CAE5401FC09" box="[451,633,908,933]" country="Iran" name="Khorasan-e Jonubi" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">South Khorasan</collectingRegion>
</materialsCitation>
, and 
<collectingRegion id="49AEF806FFAEFF9BFD784CAE5567FC09" box="[692,799,908,933]" country="Iran" name="Khorasan-e Shomali" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Khorasan</collectingRegion>
Razavi to 
<collectingRegion id="49AEF806FFAEFF9BFC544CAE558AFC09" box="[920,1010,908,933]" country="Iran" name="Semnan" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Semnan</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion id="49AEF806FFAEFF9BFBE54CAE52A8FC0F" box="[1065,1232,908,933]" country="Iran" name="Golestan" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Golestan Prov.</collectingRegion>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD536E4FFAEFF9BFF5B4C92521EFC41" blockId="34.[151,1437,692,1112]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
HABITAT. Hard loess soils, sometimes with admixture of sand or pebbles, and with ephemeral vegetation. The Iranian populations occur between 1300 and 
<quantity id="4C929B01FFAEFF9BFD434CF6549CFC47" box="[655,740,980,1005]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" unit="m" value="1700.0">1700 m</quantity>
a.s.l. (
<bibRefCitation id="EFFB4B15FFAEFF9BFCE14CF65222FC41" author="Leviton, A. E. &amp; Anderson, S. C." box="[813,1114,980,1005]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="163 - 206" refId="ref56924" refString="Leviton, A. E. &amp; Anderson, S. C. (1970) The Amphibians and reptiles of Afghanistan, a checklist and key to the herpetofauna. Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, 38, 163 - 206." type="journal article" year="1970">Leviton &amp; Anderson 1970</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C370656FFFAEFF9BFF5B4CDA536FFB99" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BD536E4FFAEFF9BFF5B4CDA536FFB99" blockId="34.[151,1437,692,1112]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
REMARKS. Some authors considered this species to be a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D67FFAEFF9BFC254CDB52FFFBBC" baseAuthorityName="Strauch" baseAuthorityYear="1876" box="[1001,1159,1015,1040]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Eremias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="intermedia">
<emphasis id="B91EEAF6FFAEFF9BFC254CDB52FFFBBC" box="[1001,1159,1015,1040]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">E. intermedia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFFB4B15FFAEFF9BFB574CD55332FBBC" author="Nikolsky, A. M." box="[1179,1354,1015,1040]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="95 - 98" refId="ref60725" refString="Nikolsky, A. M. (1903) On the species of reptiles collected by N. A. Zarudny in Eastern Persia in 1901 [in Russian]. Annuaire Musee Zoologique de l'Academie Imperiale des Sciences de St. - Petersbourg, 8, 95 - 98." type="journal article" year="1903">Nikolsky 1903</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFB4B15FFAEFF9BFA904CD553E0FBBC" author="Nikolsky, A. M." box="[1372,1432,1015,1040]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="260 - 301" refId="ref60776" refString="Nikolsky, A. M. (1907) Reptiles and Amphibians collected by N. A. Zarudny in Persia 1903 - 1904 [in Russian]. Annuaire Musee Zoologique de l'Academie Imperiale des Sciences de St. - Petersbourg, 10, 260 - 301." type="journal article" year="1907">1907</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFB4B15FFAEFF9BFF5B4B3E5734FB99" author="Boulenger, G. A." box="[151,332,1052,1077]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" refId="ref47880" refString="Boulenger, G. A. (1921) Monograph of the Lacertidae. II. Longmans, Green &amp; Co. and British Museum (Natural History), 451 pp." type="book" year="1921">Boulenger 1921</bibRefCitation>
) and even 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFB4B15FFAEFF9BFE0A4B3E5405FB99" author="Anderson, S. C." box="[454,637,1052,1077]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="417 - 498" refId="ref45083" refString="Anderson, S. C. (1963) Amphibians and reptiles from Iran. Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, 31, 417 - 498." type="journal article" year="1963">Anderson (1963</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFB4B15FFAEFF9BFD454B3E54BAFB99" author="Anderson, S. C." box="[649,706,1052,1077]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" refId="ref45318" refString="Anderson, S. C. (1999) The lizards of Iran. Society for the Study of Amphibians and Reptiles, Oxford, Ohio, 442 pp." type="book" year="1999">1999</bibRefCitation>
) was not convinced that these two forms are distinct.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
